article.headline: Drexel 74, Ball State 70
article.story: MUNCIE, Ind. (AP) -- Phil Goss scored 26 points, including 7-of-12 3-pointers, as a late rally lifted Drexel to a 74-70 win over Ball State on Saturday night. The Cardinals (12-11) dominated the first half with superior shooting that put them ahead by up to 14 points before the Dragons began their surge, aided by Sean Brooks, who had 25 points and 10 rebounds for the night. Ball State held a 35-26 halftime lead, but Drexel -- buoyed by superior free throw shooting and Goss' five 3-pointers in the second half -- sliced into the Cardinals' lead. The two teams traded leads three times in the final 6:51 before a Goss 3-pointer at 4:18 made it 65-63 Drexel as the Dragons (14-10) grabbed the lead for good. Goss' last 3-pointer, with 33 seconds to go, put Drexel ahead by five, 72-67. Ball State's Darron Yates responded with his own 3-point play with 25 seconds remaining to cut Drexel's lead to 72-70. The Cardinals then called a timeout and when the game resumed Peyton Stovall fouled Drexel's Kenell Sanchez, who made both of his free throws to seal the Dragons' win. Terrance Chapman led Ball State with 23 points, while Julien Mills added 20.
